cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper is about improving network measurement capabilities through the use of counter arrays. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the trade-off between precision and space, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves separating flows into buckets, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
